commit.message: Clean stuff up a bit

Revise the core code to only use necessary code

Pomodoro was originally built in a hackathon relying heavily on code
from tonyvanriet/lunchbot. Most of the code that ran in core was doing
absolutely nothing. That code has been removed. I now know what
everything does that's in the file.

Exit cleanly on no connection

If there's no connection, or an error connecting, the program would
print two stack traces, pointing blame at netty and aleph. This doesn't
seem fair. It's not their fault. Instead now a simple set of messages is
printed and then the program exits (with a failure status of 1).

Rely on the new dnd module methods of the client

I've written a dnd module for the clj-slack-api fork. This uses those
methods to simplify the status dnd file greatly.
Add some more photos from the hackathon

Make the api-token immutable

The api-token variable is slurped at the first requirement of it in
core. This makes it always available. Having the api-token as a
:^dynamic var is odd because it's only read once. It will only have one
value because api-tokens do not change

Remove code copied from slack integration

The basic methods used to access the api were removed. This is due to
the new convenience function call-and-get-response

Use the wrapper for do not disturb calls

The wrapper implemented in the previous commit is useful to remove the
mutes dependency in the pomodoro.status namespace. It also makes the
code a bit cleaner and easier to read

Add a wrapper function for call-and-get-resp.

This wrapper just interjects my api-token into the parameters, making
dependencies cleaner

Use convenience method for api calls on get-names

I wrote a convenience method for the useage of api-methods in the slack
client
Rename functions for clarity

Check if a timer is running before ending

The end reply method now checks if a timer was running before it ends
it. Returns a statement:

- The timer isn't on.
or
- Pomodoro cancelled.

Depending on the condition of the timer
Ignore case on the command regexes

Make the timer an atom

Atoms should be more suitable for what I'm trying to do with the timer.
Making it multiple different values is useful as a timer. The different
values are different futures, which contain the response.

Update deps

This is possible because of new active developement of the
clj-slack-client library
Remove unused dep in core

Delete the core and restore functionality

This version also works. Duplicate functions in the core have been
deleted and now all functions are split into their respective files.
Note that in order to correct this code to run properly, I had to remove
several circular deps and add a new file, as well as make many smaller
changes. Do not go back to the previous commit for any reason

Segment functions into appropriate ns's

During the hackathon the file just needed to work. Now the functions are
split into appropriate files. This will make it easier to read and
develop. N.B. the project still runs but none of these files have been
implemented yet. The core still needs to be reduced
Add a square pomo picture for the app

Update the link for the bot API

This one will bring you to the correct link
